        ]
      },
      "description": "Authenticate using a Google OAuth access token.\n\n**Auth:** not required.\n\n**Query params:** none\n\n**Request body validation:**\n- `access_token`: required|string\n- `device_name`: sometimes|nullable|string|max:255\n\n**Authentication mode:**\nUses `X-Auth-Mode` (`token`|`cookie`).\n- **Token mode:** returns access/refresh tokens in JSON\n- **Cookie mode:** sets HttpOnly central auth cookies and omits token fields from JSON\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Verifies Google access token with Socialite\n- Creates or links a local account by provider+subject/email\n- Returns `tfa_required` flow when user has two-factor enabled\n- Requires verified social email for first-time linking"
